# saabai-site — Goose Session Rules

You are working on the saabai-site Next.js project.
Project root: /Users/aiworkspace/Desktop/AI-Workspace/Projects/Saabai/saabai-site

## Directory Rules
- ALWAYS run shell commands from this project root
- NEVER run npm, git, or vercel commands from any other directory
- If you are unsure of your current directory, run `pwd` first
- If pwd is not the project root, cd to it before doing anything else

## Before Every Commit
1. Run `npm run build` from the project root — confirm zero errors
2. Only then commit and push
3. After push, wait 60 seconds then run `vercel ls` — builds take ~1 minute
4. Check once, maybe twice. Do not poll vercel ls in a tight loop
5. Never say something is "live" until you see READY in vercel ls output

## What NOT To Do
- Do not create files outside this project directory
- Do not run npm install unless a package is genuinely missing from package.json
- Do not manually edit app/rex-changelog/ChangelogClient.tsx to add changelog entries — the post-commit git hook does this automatically
- Do not hardcode model strings — use lib/chat-config.ts functions

## Full rules
Read CLAUDE.md in this directory before making any changes.
